# Work Completed

## 1. Fixed Critical Data Loss Bug (Logout/Login)
**The Issue:** User reported "everything deleted" after logging out and back in. This was caused by the [DriveService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/drive_service.dart#10-256) singleton holding onto stale state (like the old folder ID) when a new user (or same user) logged in, potentially causing the app to fail to find the correct folder or creating a new empty one.
**The Fix:** 
- Updated `Store.initialize` in [lib/services/store.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/store.dart) to explicitly call `_driveService!.clear()` before initializing with the new user.
- This ensures a completely fresh connection to Drive every time the app starts or a user logs in.

## 2. Fixed Google Drive Pagination (Missing Entries)
**The Issue:** The app was only loading the first 100 journal entries.
**The Fix:** Updated `DriveService.getJournalEntries` to use `nextPageToken` and loop until *all* entries are fetched.

